The paper deals with the theoretical notions of graph classes with bounded expansion and nowhere dense graphs, which are typically studied in the subfields of graph theory and combinatorics. The paper also focuses on the Dominating Set problem, which is a classic problem in computational complexity theory and graph algorithms. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), cs.CC (Computational Complexity), cs.CG (Computational Geometry), and cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory).
